feel free to ignore me but you have great judgement & I was curious for your thoughts on smth I’m wondering: tommy's clearly committed to his acting & has dialed the intensity up once again, which is...
3:51 PM
The answer, not the ask. It’s a bit old but it’s so good.
3:52 PM
He’s very distant, he’s very muted. He’s seen a lot of shit. His apparent “lack of care” when it comes to things like his death - or his friend’s deaths - can, I think, be interpreted as a seriously traumatized reaction to having constant violence inflicted on you from a young age. It’s almost like he’s depersonalized.
a kid who’s so deeply, like, shell-shocked, that he can’t bring himself to care that much about his own life and safety, because it’s been proven to him, over and over, that he has no control over what happens to him.
  • Maybe this isn’t the c!Tubbo people want to see, but it’s kind of the c!Tubbo we have? And I think understanding that gives us a different expectation of the kind of clingy duo scenes we’re going to get in canon. c!Tubbo doesn’t show extreme emotion, he doesn’t respond well in the moment, and if anything is too bad or too difficult he goes into shut-down mode. He literally just doesn’t deal with it. He can’t

Anyway, analysis thoughts unrelated to the most recent streams, but have just been on my mind
8:56 PM
I feel like there’s a chance that Fundy and Wilbur will never have a reconciliation arc. And I feel this for a couple of reasons.
8:58 PM
For one, I don’t think in terms of Wilbur’s redemption and healing, that Fundy has been an anyway given a significant amount of focus in comparison to say Tommy or Tubbo
8:59 PM
I think at this point, Tommy and Tubbo reconciling with Wilbur is bound to happen and even necessary to Wilbur’s arc, but Fundy has rarely if even been talked abt in the burger arc and there’s rlly no signs of him appearing anytime soon
9:00 PM
Another thing is, in the eyes of many of the audience, Fundy isn’t part of the “group.” There’s the L’ManTrio that consists of Wilbur, Tommy and Tubbo and are frequently discussed in fan works and metas, but Fundy is often left out in fir gotten
9:01 PM
So not only has the Fundy-Wilbur reconciliation been built up in canon, but it’s also not rlly been built up in the minds of the audience compared to other characters and their reconciliation with Wilbur
9:03 PM
Also, I’m not sure if Wilbur and Fundy making up would strictly be good for Fundy’s arc? Like I think it’d be nice and I’m not privy to what direction Fundy is going to take his character, but I’m not sure if making the culmination of Fundy’s arc being Wilbur acknowledging him would be a good conclusion
9:05 PM
Like, maybe it comes after, but before that, I think it would be more important for Fundy to find happiness with himself and learn not to unhealthy lean/rely on outside validation, as he has so often been doing throughout the dsmp
9:06 PM
I think Fundy learning to be happy with himself and his accomplishments, and then having Wilbur finally acknowledge him would be better, since it’s would be giving Fundy the validation always wanted, but now he no longer needs that validation
9:08 PM
Anyway, less analysis and more of a hot take, but while I don’t think Wilbur was a terrible father, I also don’t get the argument that he was a good/great parent either

just a lil guy🥚🍄☀ 2/16/2022 5:32 PM
okie okie so i was doing a lil outlining for tmod but i stumbled across some thoughts that were more dsmp analysis and i have GOT to say my funky little words
5:34 PM
okie so. i'm something of a boober, and i adore analyzing wtf goes on in cranboo lil head, and it was thinking about why benchtrio work well together, why do clingyduo work well, why do beeduo work well, and why do alliumduo just work well
5:38 PM
so, ranboo for example has a strict personal code of 'as long as others aren't hurt.' he's flexible when it comes to himself, like he will allow himself to be hurt so long as others aren't, BUT he's also privately self serving. if others seemingly can't be reasoned with, then he will either flee or privately go about helping. either way he does this alone to try and ensure no one gets hurt. the point is, he falls back on his morals because he can't trust that others don't want to hurt others, but he can trust that he doesn't want to hurt others
just a lil guy🥚🍄☀ 2/16/2022 5:47 PM
so, why does he work well with ctubbo? now, tubblings correct me if i'm wrong, but tubbo's personal code isn't the same as ranboo's because to him, people are going to get hurt and hurt others. that's just the way it is, so his code is along the lines of 'as long as i am safe and those closest to me are safe.' him being safe directly ties to others though, because as long as he can keep moving, he can keep protecting. he won't be needlessly hurt, and this clashes with ranboo's code, BUT works well with How they both do things. both of them do things alone, and we've seen tubbo shoulder some heavy things by himself. god i hope this is making sense, i've got so much to say lmao so like, neither of them question why the other does something that they only find out about later, because they both get it. they're like the definition of being alone but together
5:52 PM
BUT with ranboo and ctommy, they're different on BOTH accounts! tommy's code is rooted in self preservation. people get hurt sure, but he'll fight to try and make sure that he is safe and other's are safe. he needs to do this With others, because if he does it without others it destroys him. we've seen how it's destroyed him. it's why alliumduo works well in the end, because they pick up each others pitfalls, if that makes sense...
5:53 PM
i'm steadily losing my words but i've still gotta talk about clingyduo lmao
just a lil guy🥚🍄☀ 2/16/2022 6:01 PM
okie so, clingyduo work cause they're personal codes are similar, but with different emphasis. tommy protects himself and others, tubbo protects himself to protect others. tommy's circle extends to many people, while tubbo's is smaller. oh god. where did the words go. uuuh hmm so, in this aspect, they can work well together. tommy helps keep tubbo head up, and tubbo keeps tommy grounded. it's interesting because they do things differently, tubbo goes it alone, tommy can't, and this often causes friction between them. (ahem the discs were worth more than you ever were...) BUT this friction ends up bringing them closer (yes the compasses make me cry okie ;;;;;; ow)

also something i think is interesting is that ive picked up on a couple of different goals people on the smp have, and it's very interesting how much it speaks to their character: tommy prioritizes little bits and humor, power towers and cuck sheds. He finds enjoyment in the little things, in the simplicity of life. tubbo, on the other hand, goes nearly fully in the opposite direction - he focuses on large projects. a house that takes fifteen hours to build, a bee farm that takes eight. Farming wither skulls and fighting the wither to get a beacon. Fundy is more of a prankster - going around and stealing stuff, selling it back to the person he stole it from in the first place. making first his long schlong and then his longer schlong and then attempting to make his longest schlong. Filling people's houses up with chickens Purpled tends to focus on either preparing for combat or making his UFO/area 51. He also is the only member of the server who hacks - he uses the badlion client, he utilizes freecam, etc. He's focused on gaining an advantage over the other members of the server, and he talks up a big game about how he's going to attack people once he's attained enough power but his actual interactions with others speak differently - they are, by and large, innocent and playful. He doesn't go out of his way to kill anyone, and he goes along with the court cases in a way that it seems he understands the importance of some level of order. sapnap is very focused on keeping the server pristine - he spends a large amount of time every stream cleaning up other's messes, lamenting about how if it was just him, george, and dream on the server these messes wouldn't exist. He works on projects, too, but those tend to be more in conjunction with others, perserving the pristineness of the server in a less literal sense (the interpersonal connections) wow i almost hit character limit with this LMAOOO

🐸 3/7/2022 7:33 PM
Hello covers it’s a semi-regularly occurring episode of Thoughts With Junior Time (edited)
7:34 PM
So I was thinking, because of bbh’s stream tonight, about the nature of collaborative projects on the server.
7:36 PM
Moreover, the nature of the way that there’s kind of a culture in-universe of putting your personal gripes aside for the sake of building, gathering resources, terraforming, farming, etc.
7:37 PM
So like. A lot of those tasks are done on streams that aren’t typically considered ‘lore’, and for that reason it’s very easy to consider them non-canonical - but I think it’s far more interesting to consider those actions to be canon (edited)
7:39 PM
Because I think it’s fascinating that overwhelmingly, those tasks are performed as a group effort? Since the very first days of the server, people have done things together.
7:41 PM
And of course on a more meta level that’s obviously because streams with other people make for far more interesting content - but if you look at that in-universe, it’s a part of the culture of the server that’s really intriguing!
